Direct Data is an option for querying live Salesforce data without having to set up replication or create datasets. With Direct Data, you can query Salesforce objects in the dashboard designer’s explorer and edit Salesforce Object Query Language (SOQL) queries in the query editor.

For best performance, use Direct Data only where data changes often and scheduled dataflows aren’t frequent enough. Queries on Salesforce objects with a large number of records could increase query time. Use filters to limit the data that's queried.

Direct Data is accessible only in the dashboard designer. After a Direct Data widget is added to a dashboard, you can select Explore from the widget’s dropdown and open a Direct Data exploration in a new tab.

Maximum limits on CRM Analytics API calls and on queries apply to Direct Data:

* Maximum concurrent CRM Analytics API calls per org: 100
* Maximum CRM Analytics API calls per user per hour: 10,000
* Maximum concurrent queries per organization: 50 per platform
* Maximum concurrent queries per user: 10
title: Optimizing Salesforce Direct Data Queries
